                                        <fixVersion>2.1 beta1</fixVersion>
                                    <component>Feature/2i Index</component>
                        <due></due>
                            <votes>2</votes>
                                    <watches>5</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13870555" author="mafernandez" created="Tue, 14 Jan 2014 09:13:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In order to avoid this null pointer exception, we shouldn&apos;t assume that highestSelectivityIndex (which is a SecondaryIndex) has a IndexCfs because that depends on the implementation type.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, a nice way to solve this issue would be to include an abstract method in the SecondaryIndex class, add a implementation of the method where we really know there is a IndexCfs and otherwise delegate the implementation of this method to those who are creating a custom 2i.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I submit a patch that implements this solution.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13870957" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 14 Jan 2014 17:45:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;WDYT &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=beobal&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;beobal&quot;&gt;beobal&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13872111" author="adelapena" created="Wed, 15 Jan 2014 14:23:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have been assigned to this bug, the provided patch seems to work fine.&lt;br/&gt;
Could the reviewer please review (and, hopefully, commit) the patch?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13872128" author="aagea" created="Wed, 15 Jan 2014 14:36:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13872138" author="beobal" created="Wed, 15 Jan 2014 14:45:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 patch looks good to me. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In fact, the same issue affects Solr backed indexes in DSE and our approach is the same.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13872304" author="mafernandez" created="Wed, 15 Jan 2014 17:35:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve been running some tests with this patch and there were no errors.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13872342" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 15 Jan 2014 18:09:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
